an class=title>   Attending Or Leading A Raid? - UPDATED 03/03 </span><hr size=1> Raiding isn't the primary focus of EQ for Rutabagas.  But, if they are done right, they can be fun, and give a nice break away from exp grinding.  Sound like fun?  Maybe you'd like to lead some raids?  <br>
<br>
Before you do, look at the following things that are essential for a successful raid.  <br>
<br>
First of all, if you want to have a raid, you have to be the one to lead it!  You can't expect anyone to do the dirtywork for you, unless that someone offers.<br>
<br>
Those who can, are those who do!<br>
<br>
Requirements:<br>
 <br>
1- Don't expect everyone is going to show up. Like I said before...  we're not a mandatory raiding guild.  Some of our members HATE raiding.  So why have a raiding policy?  Errr..  because I love to type!  -  Wait, no...  because some of our members do like it.  Raids happen and @#%$ happens.  sometimes, the two go hand in hand.  This is to guide you through the rough parts.  <br>
<br>
If you simply must raid, then Be on time.  Be prepared.  If a raid is at 7, please don't log on at 7:15  and start looking for a port in guildchat... or I'll beat you over the head with a smelly trolll boot.<br>
 <br>
2. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> Raid leaders must know the zone,</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> .. and what everyone should be doing.  For example, if people need to have certain resists up above 100 that needs to be communicated before the raid.  If AE spells are not allowed, that needs to be said, etc, etc..  People will be showing up and looking at you for instruction.<br>
 <br>
3. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> A &quot;Main Tank&quot; (MT)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> should be appointed and a back up MT should be appointed,  A suggestion is to have a corpse puller should be appointed, and make sure everyone should consent the corpse puller and all of this should be done before the raid begins in case of linkdeath.<br>
 <br>
4. A chat channel should be made.  In case of severe whipe out, log onto an alt and join the chat channel.<br>
 <br>
5. Raid leader should have their objective planned out and be aware of other guilds in the zone when we enter, and be able to communicate to the people who are participating in our raid, and have a backup raid planned, if a raid flops due to another guild already being in the zone and raiding our objective.  If it so happens that there is a problem such as Rutabaga not having full force to take a spawn, and another guild advancing...  you are instructed to let them, and not interfere, not insult, not flame their entire guild on druzzilro.com.  Just have your ducks in a row next time.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
 <br>
6. The raid leader should be the one to handle problems that might arise during raids (another guild leapfrogging in past the raid party).  If there ends up being two separate raiding parties with the same objective, that raid leader should contact the other raid leader.<br>
 <br>
7. There should be no negative /ooc smacktalk clouding the public channels.  If any of my members or participants act dishonorably, or don't listen to the raid leader, they will be whacked with the 'trout of doom' by me, or any officer present.  The severity of the whack depends on the severity of the offense.  If necessary, any person who cannot comply may be removed from the raid.  <br>
<br>
 <br>
8. Have a coffin in the bank, a couple of periodots on you, and a lot of patience.<br>
 <br>
9. The raid leader should have loot rules decided upon beforehand.  This entails understanding what loot will maybe drop during the raid, who can really use it, and how it should be handed out.  The rules should be established before the raid and posted in the raid invite so that everyone is aware of how loot will be handled.<br>
 <br>
10. The raid leader needs to decide the policy concerning guests on the raid.  Is the raid restricted to just rutabaga members or are outside guests welcome to join.  And if outside guests are joining, the raid leader is responsible for deciding how those outside guests will participate in the loot and making sure the guests are aware of this decision.<br>
<br>
11. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Usage of the druzzilro.com raid board - (insert guild here) stole my epic!</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  The raid board is for posting intentions only.  Do not view it as a reservation.  It isn't.  If you tell the whole world that you're heading to Chardok at 6, and a different guild shows up there at 5:45...  you are instructed not to whine, nor to pout... and not to post a long embarassing flame on druzzilro.com about how you have been screwed.  ... flaming on the rant boards about how someone else stole your epic mob is like peeing in a wind tunnel.  Prepared to get some of what you spew, splattered back on you and your guildmates.  What you do and what you say reflects on us.  You've been warned!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   You can't stop people from jumping, steamrolling you, or leapfrogging you, but you can control how you react... and reacting with top class is the only way to win.  If you act with no class, you lose, no matter what the turnout is.<br>
<br>
We do suggest picking an OTM night, and checking the raid board and respecting the intentions of others.  We're about having fun, not ruining the fun of others...  Ever.  Period.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Lastly, other issues that we haven't thought of yet may arise in the future.  In that case, please notify an officer, so that we all can work together to come up with a solution.<br>
<br>
<br>
Have fun! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub22.ezboard.com/brutabagaparadoxforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alihjazanzibar>Alihja Zanzibar</A> at: 3/19/03 5:33:28 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub22.ezboard.com/frutabagaparadoxforumgeneraldiscussion.showPrevMessage?topicID=901.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub22.ezboard.com/frutabagaparadoxforumgeneraldiscussion.showNextMessage?topicID=901.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub22.ezboard.com/frutabagaparadoxforumgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=901.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub22.ezboard.com/frutabagaparadoxforumgeneraldiscussion.emailToFriend?topicID=901.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub22.ezboard.com/frutabagaparadoxforumgeneraldiscussion.threadControl?topicID=901.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub22.ezboard.com/frutabagaparadoxforumgeneraldiscussion.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=901.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub22.ezboard.com/frutabagaparadoxforumgeneraldiscussion.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=901.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving